      "metadata": {
        "id": "7JYVyGo2wHlm"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Multimodal Emotion Recognition\n",
        "## Training Notebook\n",
        "-Speech Pipeline: Extracts Mel-frequency cepstral coefficients (MFCCs) from the audio signals and passes them through a Bidirectional LSTM (BiLSTM) with an attention mechanism for audio-based emotion classification.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "-Text Pipeline: Leverages a pre-trained BERT bert-base-uncased architecture to process textual prosody descriptions and classify emotions based on linguistic features.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "-Fusion Pipeline (Multimodal): Combines the speech features from the BiLSTM and text features from the BERT model using a gated fusion mechanism to perform joint, multimodal emotion recognition\n"
      ]
    },
    {
